Seeing them grow has been the absolute best. 💖💖 #twins #10months

node.text:
I’m so grateful to have this amazing man in my life to raise this big bunch of kids with. He is gentle, caring, hard-working and is so full of love and gratitude 💛
I’m so glad our kiddos are half you because you’re the best. 😘
Happy Father’s Day 🥰😍

node.text:
The twins and their friend Blossom who is only two days younger than them 🌸
It was a lovely play date with our friends @blossom.and.the.boys - the babies played together and all 9 of our other kiddos played so well together at the park ❤️
It was so hard getting a photo of three busy crawling babies! Watching them all crawl around together definitely brought back memories of having baby triplets 🙈🙈🙈
If ever you are wondering if triplets is much different to twins.. the answer is yes.. yes it is 😂🤪🙃🤣

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by chloe and beans on August 27, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, child, people standing and indoor.

node.text:
Can you believe these squishy little beans turn 10 months old tomorrow? Yeah neither can I 🥺
Honestly though, I swear the 9-12 stage is my fave part of the first year 🥰 I do love newborns but I just love the cheeky, happy, smiley babies crawling all over the house! It doesn’t last long. They’ll be walking before I know it.. now Cosmo has started “cruising” or furniture walking, I’m sure it won’t be long 😳 I’ll guess he will be taking steps at about 11 months.. and Sylvie will probably take a bit longer ☺️
When did your babes start walking?? Or when did you? 👶🏼

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by chloe and beans on August 20, 2021. May be a closeup of 1 person, baby and indoor.

node.text:
Cosmo ✨

Ever since he was a tiny tot, the thing that has always been able to calm him instantly when all else fails, is playing the song “heat waves” by glass animals. I have no idea why. He just finds it soothing.
Now he’s heard the song 628399 times, and I don’t even have to play it anymore, I just sing it.. and he instantly stops crying and just looks at me like this. 🥺

Has anybody else had a baby that would settle to just one song or tune in particular? ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by chloe and beans on August 19, 2021. May be an image of 4 people, child, people standing, outdoors and tree.

node.text:
This week has been a bit intense, moving house with 8 kiddos, including twins who crawl everywhere 🙈
I shared a little in stories this week and to answer some questions.. we are renting this home and we feel so blessed to be approved for a rental because it’s very tough and competitive right now, and the area we moved to isn’t exactly abundant in rentals.
Another question was why did we move and it was to be closer to the kids’ new school 🌳
I had hoped to share more of our moving journey on YT but it’s been so busy, I haven’t had the chance to film anything! I do however, have an empty house tour to edit and upload and I’ll do that as soon as I can.
We haven’t completely finished moving but it’s getting there! We are loving the new house and are so excited to settle in and make lots of new memories here ❤️🏡🌳

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by chloe and beans on August 10, 2021 tagging @burleighwagon. May be an image of 1 person, child, standing, brick wall and outdoors.

node.text:
Adventures out with the tiny ones.
It’s funny going out with just the twins whilst the kids are at school and having people assume they’re my only kids.. A few days ago we were looking through a rental home and there was a lady also looking with her son and he needed to use the bathroom. She said something about how you can’t take kids anywhere, before looking at our twins and saying “Twins?? Good luck with that!” 😳
I just chuckled politely but am always thinking .. if only they knew 😆🤣
Speaking of looking through homes.. I have an exciting update I’m going to post to YouTube either tonight or tomorrow 🏡🥰✨

node.text:
🎒The kids before school yesterday.. bed hair and all 😴 
It’s been a few months since we transitioned from homeschooling to school, and we are still struggling to get out the door on time 😆 even though we all get up 2 hours before we leave the house 😳
Come on school veterans, do you have any tips for us to make these mornings go a little smoother? Or is it a crazy rush in your house too? 😝

node.text:
My “middle kids” ❤️
I know in a family of three kiddos, there is the oldest, middle and youngest.
And maybe in bigger families the oldest is just meant to be the oldest child and the youngest is the single youngest.
But generally I consider my two eldest to be “the oldest” as they are only 11 months apart and are similar in maturity. I also have two youngest as they’re twins. 🤷🏼‍♀️ So these four are kind of like our middle kids. The triplets were all “the youngest” until the twins were born but now they’ve joined Felix in the middle 😆

If you have more than 3 kids, how many do you consider oldest/middle/youngest? 🤔🥰
